title: storybook-25-ch-1-par-1
transcription: Lara the ladybird was a special bug.

title: storybook-25-ch-2-par-1
transcription: Unlike all her friends, she had bright yellow wings.

title: storybook-25-ch-4-par-1
transcription: Each morning, Bibi Butterfly said hello.

title: storybook-25-ch-6-par-1
transcription: At school, she played with lots of friends.

title: storybook-22-ch-3-par-2
transcription: Like the leopard and the leopard cat!

title: storybook-22-ch-4-par-1
transcription: Some wild cats are the best climbers.

title: storybook-22-ch-4-par-2
transcription: Like the clouded leopard and the marbled cat!

title: storybook-22-ch-5-par-1
transcription: Some wild cats live high up in the mountains.

title: storybook-22-ch-5-par-2
transcription: Like the snow leopard and the Palla's cat!

title: storybook-22-ch-6-par-1
transcription: Some wild cats live in the desert.

title: storybook-22-ch-7-par-1
transcription: Some wild cats have hairy ears.

title: storybook-22-ch-7-par-2
transcription: Like the caracal and the lynx!

title: storybook-22-ch-8-par-1
transcription: Some wild cats love to fish.

title: storybook-22-ch-9-par-1
transcription: Some wild cats are the smallest wild cats in the world.

title: storybook-22-ch-10-par-1
transcription: Some wild cats look like house cats.

title: storybook-22-ch-10-par-2
transcription: Like the jungle cat and the golden cat!

title: storybook-22-ch-11-par-1
transcription: But they are all wild cats!

title: storybook-28-ch-11-par-1
transcription: As the birds fly away, they look back at Bounthy with a smile.

title: storybook-25-ch-8-par-1
transcription: So one day, to cheer her up, Lara’s mother painted her wings bright red.

title: storybook-25-ch-9-par-1
transcription: The next morning, nobody greeted Lara on her way to school.
